be exclusively used by your game. <br>    </p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >CPUCores will allow game-specific hyper-thread disabling/enabling.</p></li></ul><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >4) BACKGROUND / NON-GAME OPTIMIZATIONS</p><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >CPUCores examines what non-OS and non-game operations your PC is running. It will do things such as constrain non-game programs to your first processing core.</p></li></ul><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >5) EXTRAS</p><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Ability to \"START RANDOM GAME\" with 1 button click!<br>    </p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Fully supporting VR games!<br>    </p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Support for non-Steam games<br>    </p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Support for general, non-game applications like video editing, graphic design and more!<br>    </p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Convenient game sorting options makes large Steam libraries manageable<br>    </p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Incredible community surrounding the software!<br>    </p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Direct contact with the developer for suggestions on feature updates!</p></li></ul><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline crossorigin=\"anonymous\" poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/384300/extras/f9fb02da16e3ec19e975c7549858c0bf.poster.avif?t=1739668443\" width=610 height=73 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/384300/extras/f9fb02da16e3ec19e975c7549858c0bf.webm?t=1739668443\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"></video></span>The impact of how CPUCores will help with FPS depends on essentially 2 things: </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >#1 Your PC Hardware</p><p class=\"bb_pa